',{id:"state_minimum_wage_vs_living_wage_gap",title:"State minimum wage vs. MIT living wage by state - the gap between the law and reality",sub:"California minimum wage: $16/hr. MIT living wage for single adult: $22.86. Gap: $6.86. Mississippi minimum wage: $7.25 (federal). MIT living wage: $17.28. Gap: $10.03. Every state has a gap - but the gap is largest in the states with the lowest wages and least safety nets.",type:"MAP",geo:"us_state",fmt:"State choropleth",tbl:"DOL state minimum wage data + MIT Living Wage Calculator (both public)",section:"Labor Force",ext:["ACS 5-year estimates: MHI, poverty rate, population by geography (Census API - free, tidycensus)","BEA Regional: GDP + personal income per capita by state (apps.bea.gov - free)","Census Population Estimates: annual population by state/county (census.gov - free)","BLS LAUS: unemployment + labor force by state (bls.gov - free)"],vars:["manufacturing_hourly_wages_state","median_household_income"],join:["pct_under_25k","rep_pct","state_unemployment_rate"],sc:{emotional:8,relatability:9,surprise:7,tension:7,visual:7,data_ready:9,originality:5},vs:76,tags:"minimum wage living wage state California $16 $22.86 gap $6.86 Mississippi $7.25 $17.28 gap $10.03 every state gap largest lowest wages DOL MIT Calculator"}',
